one.name: McSwiggans
one.description: McSwiggan’s is part of the fabric of Galway life, a landmark within this vibrant city for over 30 years. It’s has been seeping up stories since it evolved from a lively country stores trading potatoes in the iconic Woodquay Market, into a sanctuary to catch-up, hide-away, eat, drink, laugh and make memories.

two.name: Rearden's
two.description: Cavernous, shabby-chic bar and live music venue, also offering sports on TV, sandwiches and pies.

three.name: Mary's Bar & Hardware
three.description: Mary's will have what you need, from a pint of plain to a can of WD40.
